                why: 'Whatever programming language you use — Python, Java, or any other — you always give the computer a step-by-step recipe. This is also true in software testing: writing "test login" is not enough. You must spell out which user, which password, which action, and what result to expect. A test case and an algorithm share the same mental structure: explicit steps, in order, with a clear expected result.',
